```R
stop_index <- sapply(estimated_surv_probs, function(s) {
  ind <- which(s < 0.5)
  if (length(ind) > 0) {
    min(ind)
  } else {
    length(surv_prob_all[["time"]])
  }
})
```

This code checks whether there are survival probabilities less than 0.5 for each remaining patient. If there are, it finds the minimum index, and if not, it uses the highest time value from the `survfit` object.

Now, you shouldn't see warnings, and `additional_survival_time_sim` should contain the estimated additional survival time for each remaining patient based on the fitted Cox proportional hazards model with piecewise hazard rates.

